          "",
          "Authors use features from mulitple assignments. In essence, they monitor the submission, grade, etc… for each assigment k in a total of 27 assignments. ",
          "Unspecified",
          "-",
          "-",
          "Assignments 21 and 22 were found to be assignments where students tended to fail the most and this was, in fact, later confirmed by the teaching staff.  \n\nThe sequence also allows the visibility of specific attrition points: 33% quit after Assignment 2, and only 35% participate in the final assignment.",
          "Identification of points of hurt can be used by educators to improve the curriculum.",
          "The work is divided into multiple Studies. The first study involves the creation of a set of submission trajectories and creating a graph network. ",
